@API_HostAddress = http://localhost:5210

### Health check
GET {{API_HostAddress}}/api/cleanmap/health
Accept: application/json

###

### Get all reports (public)
GET {{API_HostAddress}}/api/cleanmap/reports
Accept: application/json

###

### Signup
POST {{API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
	"username": "testuser",
	"email": "test@example.com",
	"password": "Password1"
}

###

### Login
POST {{API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
	"email": "test@example.com",
	"password": "Password1"
}

###

### Refresh token (uses HttpOnly cookie automatically)
POST {{API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/refresh

###

### Get current user (requires Bearer token)
# Replace <ACCESS_TOKEN> with the token from login/signup response
GET {{API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN>

###

### Logout (uses HttpOnly cookie automatically)
POST {{API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/logout

###

### Create report (requires auth + CSRF token)
POST {{API_HostAddress}}/api/cleanmap/reports
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN>
X-XSRF-TOKEN: <XSRF_TOKEN_FROM_COOKIE>

{
	"lat": 42.6977,
	"lng": 23.3219,
	"address": "Central Blvd, Sofia",
	"tags": ["Plastic"],
	"notes": "Overflowing bin",
	"photoBefore": "data:image/jpeg;base64,PLACEHOLDER",
	"status": "dirty"
}

###

### Mark as cleaned (requires auth + CSRF token)
POST {{API_HostAddress}}/api/cleanmap/reports/rep_example/clean
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN>
X-XSRF-TOKEN: <XSRF_TOKEN_FROM_COOKIE>

{
	"photoAfter": "data:image/jpeg;base64,PLACEHOLDER"
}

###
